headline: UDR: Q4 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The real estate investment trust, based in Highlands Ranch, Colorado, said it had funds from operations of $227.4 million, or 64 cents per share, in the period. The average estimate of six analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for funds from operations of 64 cents per share. Funds from operations is a closely watched measure in the REIT industry.

headline: UDR, Inc. Announces Fourth Quarter and Full-Year 2025 Results, Establishes 2026 Guidance Ranges and Increases Dividend
summary: DENVER, February 09, 2026--UDR, Inc. (the "Company") (NYSE: UDR), announced today its fourth quarter and full-year 2025 results, and has posted a related Investor Presentation to its website at ir.udr.com. Net Income, Funds from Operations ("FFO"), and FFO as Adjusted ("FFOA") per diluted share for the quarter and full-year ended December 31, 2025, are detailed below.
